==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muraena
<hw>Mu*rae"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of large eels of the family
<fam>Muraenidae</fam>. They differ from the common eel in lacking
pectoral fins and in having the dorsal and anal fins continuous. The
murry (<spn>Muraena Helenae</spn>) of Southern Europe was the muraena of
the Romans. It is highly valued as a food fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

